INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '6c8b5290-a198-416b-9e7a-e7fa6cd7929e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Ethereum Bridges — Lock/Mint, Canonical vs Third-Party, and What Goes Wrong$escape$,
  $escape$Ethereum bridges use a lock-and-mint model: ETH or ERC-20s are locked in a contract on the source chain while a synthetic representation is minted on the destination. Unwinding burns the synthetic and releases the original.

Canonical bridges — Optimism's L1StandardBridge (0x99C9fc46f92E8a1c0deC1b1747d010903E884bE1), Arbitrum's DelayedInbox, Base's native bridge — are operated by the rollup team and inherit the rollup's security model. Optimistic rollup withdrawals (L2→L1) are subject to a 7-day challenge window before finalization. L1→L2 deposits confirm in minutes.

Third-party bridges — Across Protocol, Hop, Stargate — use liquidity pools and relayers to bypass withdrawal delays, often settling in seconds. The cost: full smart-contract trust. Wormhole lost $320M (Feb 2022) and Ronin lost $625M (Mar 2022) to bridge exploits — both third-party.

Key risks to evaluate:
- Smart contract bugs in bridge or token logic
- Oracle manipulation on price-based bridges
- Liquidity fragmentation — bridged USDC ≠ native USDC until Circle's CCTP
- Source-chain reorg risk before finality is reached

Use canonical bridges when withdrawal delay is tolerable. For speed, audit third-party bridge code and check TVL concentration.$escape$,
  $escape$import { createWalletClient, http, parseEther } from "viem";
import { mainnet } from "viem/chains";

const L1_STANDARD_BRIDGE = "0x99C9fc46f92E8a1c0deC1b1747d010903E884bE1";

const abi = [{
  name: "depositETH",
  type: "function",
  inputs: [
    { name: "_minGasLimit", type: "uint32" },
    { name: "_extraData", type: "bytes" }
  ],
  stateMutability: "payable"
}] as const;

// Lock 0.1 ETH on L1 → mints ETH on Optimism L2
const hash = await walletClient.writeContract({
  address: L1_STANDARD_BRIDGE,
  abi,
  functionName: "depositETH",
  args: [200000, "0x"],
  value: parseEther("0.1"),
});$escape$,
